      Buttons are tied to an action of some kind, whether that button is on a cheese dispenser or launches the rocket that you're strapped to. On the Web, we follow similar conventions.

      ## How to Use

      This solution is perfect when the button needs to submit a form of some kind.

      __Note:__ Make sure to keep `type="submit"` on the button tag. That's what tells Internet Explorer to submit the form. This doesn't matter for anchor tags.

    .row.small-up-2.medium-up-4
      .column
        button class="button expanded primary" primary
      .column
        button class="button expanded secondary" secondary
      .column
        button class="button expanded info" info
      .column
        button class="button expanded success" success

    button class="button expanded" button expanded
